
[1]widen

   WIDEN, v.t. To make wide or wider; to extend in breadth; as, to widen a
   field; to widen a breach. [Note.--In America, females say, to widen a
   stocking.]

   WIDEN, v.i. To grow wide or wider; to enlarge; to extend itself.

   And arches widen, and long aisles extend.
